# CODEOWNERS for cosmos-sdk-feature-parity
#
# NOTE ON CONVENTION:
# Our parity data is stored in a small number of combined YAML files
# (data/features.yaml, data/retries.yaml, data/failovers.yaml) rather than
# per-SDK files. GitHub CODEOWNERS cannot path-match *inside* a file, so the
# entries below assign repo-wide review authority to all SDK leads.
#
# In practice:
#   - A PR that touches any SDK's rows MUST be approved by that SDK's lead.
#   - Reviewers should block-merge if rows for an SDK they do not own are
#     changed without that SDK lead's approval.
#   - See CONTRIBUTING.md ("Per-SDK ownership") for the ownership table.
#
# TODO(repo owner): replace the *-lead-tbd placeholders with real GitHub
# handles (or team slugs like @org/cosmos-dotnet-leads).

# Repo-wide default: any of the SDK leads can review general changes
# (tooling, site, docs). SDK-specific data changes additionally require the
# owning SDK lead per CONTRIBUTING.md.
*                       @dotnet-lead-tbd @java-lead-tbd @python-lead-tbd @go-lead-tbd @rust-lead-tbd

# Curated parity data — require broad review. Tag the specific SDK lead(s)
# in the PR per CONTRIBUTING.md.
